  "page": "Leygood (father of Lucas)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Leygood\" title=\"House Leygood\"><img alt=\"House Leygood.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/50px-House_Leygood.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/75px-House_Leygood.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/100px-House_Leygood.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Leygood</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Leygood\" title=\"House Leygood\"><img alt=\"House Leygood.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/50px-House_Leygood.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/75px-House_Leygood.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/69/House_Leygood.svg/100px-House_Leygood.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Caltrops_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Caltrops (The Rise of the Dragon).jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3b/The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/350px-The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"465\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3b/The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/525px-The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3b/The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/700px-The_Caltrops_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Leygood (far right) with the Caltrops by John McCambridge for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">Lord</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Caltrops_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Caltrops-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Leygood\" title=\"House Leygood\">House Leygood</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">Greens</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Caltrops\" title=\"Caltrops\">Caltrops</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Second_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"Second Battle of Tumbleton\">Tumbleton</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Leygood\" title=\"Lucas Leygood\">Lucas Leygood</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Leygood</b> was the head<sup id=\"cite_ref-Caltrops_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Caltrops-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Leygood\" title=\"House Leygood\">House Leygood</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leygood_(father_of_Lucas)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Leygood declared for King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a>. Like the rest of the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> who supported the greens, he joined the host of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ormund_Hightower\" title=\"Ormund Hightower\">Ormund Hightower</a> on his march to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"First Battle of Tumbleton\">First Battle of Tumbleton</a> and the death of Lord Ormund, the army was paralyzed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tumbleton\" title=\"Tumbleton\">city</a> without a clear commander and without knowing with certainty the intentions of the <a href=\"/index.php/Two_Betrayers\" title=\"Two Betrayers\">Two Betrayers</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh Hammer</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf White</a>. One night, Leygood and twelve other lords and <a href=\"/index.php/Landed_knight\" title=\"Landed knight\">landed knights</a> of the Reach assembled at an inn, the <a href=\"/index.php/Bloody_Caltrops\" title=\"Bloody Caltrops\">Bloody Caltrops</a>, to conspire against Hugh and Ulf. The <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"Second Battle of Tumbleton\">Second Battle of Tumbleton</a> broke out before the <a href=\"/index.php/Caltrops\" title=\"Caltrops\">Caltrops</a> could carry out their plans, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Leygood and most of his companions died during the battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Years later, during the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a>, a fellow Caltrops, assumed the position of <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> and appointed Leygood's son, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Leygood\" title=\"Lucas Leygood\">Lucas</a>, as the new <a href=\"/index.php/Commander_of_the_City_Watch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Commander of the City Watch\">Commander of the City Watch</a> of King's Landing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leygood_(father_of_Lucas)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Caltrops-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Caltrops_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Caltrops_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Leygood was a member of the <a href=\"/index.php/Caltrops\" title=\"Caltrops\">Caltrops</a>, a group of conspirators only composed of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Landed_knight\" title=\"Landed knight\">landed knights</a> from the Reach (<i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, <i>The Dying of the Dragons: Rhaenyra Overthrown</i>).</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Leygood_(father_of_Lucas)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Red Dragon and the Gold.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Overthrown.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align